<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Caledonian Road Station on the Piccadilly Line will be closed from 2200 to closing time from 1 June-18 July due to modernisation works taking place within the station.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>The works are part of TfL's 5-year &pound;10bn Investment Programme and are being carried out by Tube Lines.</p>
<p>The station will be closed on the above dates so floor resurfacing in the ticket hall can be carried out. </p>
<p>Other modernisation works include the decoration of the station, installation of CCTV cameras and passenger Help Points, as well as the refurbishment of the spiral staircase and lifts.</p>
<p>Modernisation works are due to be completed in February 2006.</p>
<p>Passengers travelling from/to Caledonian Road Station should use King's Cross St Pancras Station and take local buses 17, 91, N91 or 259.</p>
<p>Customers are advised to allow an extra 20 minutes to complete their journeys, especially those wishing to make last train connections.</p>
<p>For 24-hour information on all London travel, please call: 020 7222 1234 or visit <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">TfL's website</a>.<br></p>
